1. How to login to any site if it is showing an Authentication Pop-Up for Username and Password?
Solution:
driver.get("http://username:password@website.com");
or It can be handled by providing username and password in auth popup
driver.get("http://github.com");
Alert authAlert = driver.switchTo().alert();
authAlert.sendKeys("username" + "\n" + "password");
authAlert.accept();


2. How to click on a hyperlink in Selenium?
Solution:
WebElement link = driver.findElement(By.linkText("Link Text"));
link.click();

3. How do you perform drag-and-drop operations in Selenium WebDriver?
Solution:
WebElement sourceElement = driver.findElement(By.id("source"));
WebElement targetElement = driver.findElement(By.id("target"));

Actions actions = new Actions(driver);
actions.dragAndDrop(sourceElement, targetElement).perform();


4.What are the different types of Selenium navigation commands? How do they help the user? 
Solution:
driver.navigate().to("http://github.com");
driver.navigate().back();
driver.navigate().forward();
driver.navigate().refresh();

5.Create a Selenium script in Java to handle an alert on a webpage.
Solution:
Alert alert = driver.switchTo().alert();
alert.accept(); (or) alert.dismiss(); (or) alert.sendKeys("Text");


